			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Because people keep asking me: Mark and I spoke about this on the phone today.  We can't reasonably change this behavior on Windows, though we are evaluating workarounds.  My suggestion is this:

1. Just move BSS to the next 64KiB multiple to unblock the glibc work.

2. Remove the broken zero-fill "feature" on Linux.

3. Make the Linux map call work the same way as on Windows, if we're concerned about platform differences like that.

